    "recap_headline": "Miami Ohio University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "DeKALB, Ill. \u2013\nMiami fell in 10 innings to the Northern Illinois Huskies Friday in a 17-13 home-run fest that featured four home runs for each team.\nTommy Harrison\nled the RedHawks in RBIs with six, hitting a solo homer and a grand slam. Miami falls to 14-6 (5-2 MAC) with the win while NIU moves to 11-7 (4-3 MAC).\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nMiami struck first, putting up one run in the second inning.\nDominic Krupinski\nstole second and\nIgnacio Gonzalez\ndoubled to right field to make it 1-0.\nRyan Novak\nand\nEvan Appelwick\nhit back-to-back home runs in the third, extending the lead to 3-0.\nA walk, single, and double put two on the board for the Huskies in the bottom of the third. Two more singles and a home run gave NIU a 6-3 lead.\nThe RedHawks battled back in the fifth, starting the inning with three straight singles from\nMarcus Dierks\n, Novak, and Appelwick. Harrison hit a grand slam to propel Miami back into the lead, 7-6.\nA solo homer by NIU tied the game in the bottom of the fifth. Another solo home in the sixth gave the Huskies the lead back at 8-7.\nHarrison hit his second home run of the day in the top of the seventh to tie the game again at 8-8.\nMiami went on a tear in the eighth, scoring five more runs to make it 13-8. After a single and two walks, Harrison took an RBI HBP to score one run and a sac fly by\nCarson Raether\nscored another. Gonzalez came up with a two-RBI double and Mason Briedenbach capped off the inning with a single to score Miami's 13th run.\nThe Huskies answered with five runs of their own, tying the ballgame at 13-13 with five hits. A scoreless ninth took the game to extras.\nTwo walks and a single loaded the bases for NIU in the 10th. The Huskies hit a walk-off grand slam to finish out their 10-inning win.\nMIAMI GAME NOTES:\nDierks went 3-for-5 with two runs.\nNovak went 2-for-4 with three runs and an RBI.\nAppelwick went 2-for-5 with three runs and an RBI.\nHarrison went 2-for-4 with three runs and six RBIs.\nGonzalez went 2-for-5 with a run and three RBIs.\nBreidenbach went 2-for-4 with an RBI.\nUP NEXT:\nGame two against the Huskies is scheduled for 3 p.m. tomorrow. The series will conclude with a 2 p.m. game on Sunday.",
